## 8. Requirement -> Feature Traceability Matrix

| R# | Requirement | Coverage |
|----|-------------|---------|
| R1 | Professional frontend + backend website | Demo: Vite+React frontend + client-side JS data module as mock backend layer. Proposal narrative: explains architecture approach. |
| R2 | Visually appealing, brand-communicating design | Demo: bespoke design system (charcoal/parchment/gold, Cormorant+DM Sans, editorial asymmetric layout). |
| R3 | User-friendly interface | Demo: split-pane with sticky filters, keyboard-accessible inputs, responsive layout, logical hierarchy. |
| R4 | High-quality portfolio work | Demo + cover letter: clean component structure, zero console errors, responsive across breakpoints. |
| R5 | Reasonable timeframe and budget | Addressed in proposal narrative (scoped delivery, clear handoff). Not demoed. |
| R6 | Property listing display and browsing | Demo: PropertyList with sortable, filterable, searchable cards. |
| R7 | Mock database of real estate properties | Demo: `properties.js` with 25 properties (houses, condos, penthouses, villas, estates) across 10+ global cities. |
| R8 | List view for property browsing | Demo: PropertyList panel with filter/sort/search controls; card click opens PropertyDetail modal. |
| R9 | Map view for property discovery | Demo: MapView with Leaflet 1.9.4, CARTO Voyager tiles, custom price-pin DivIcons, flyTo on selection. |
| R10 | Property images only | Demo: all 25 Unsplash images are architectural/property photography (exteriors, interiors, skylines, estates); no unrelated stock. |
| R11 | Design not AI-generated | Demo: 28 AI-tell patterns excluded per research checklist; 8 human-craft signals applied (asymmetric layout, extreme type contrast, editorial whitespace, custom pin styling, horizontal card layout, opinionated palette, thin gold rule accents, left-aligned hero copy). |

All 11 requirements addressed. 10 demoed directly, 1 (R5) via proposal narrative only.

---

## handoff

- **Produced:** Full plan, ready for builder. Design system fully specified (hex palette, Google Fonts, layout rules). Tech stack confirmed (Vite + React 18 + Leaflet 1.9.4, no cluster lib, CARTO tiles). 13-file budget. 25 property image URLs in pre-researcher.out. All 11 requirements mapped.
- **Decisions:** D1, full build (10/10), frontend-only, no mw-backend. Favorites via localStorage. No Leaflet.markercluster (jitter + zoom 3 instead). No page routing (view state in App.jsx). Hero band uses left-aligned Cormorant Garamond display type over full-bleed property image.
- **Next needs:** Builder should read pre-researcher.out Section D for all 25 image URLs and Section E for Leaflet init/sync code snippets. Scaffold from mn-state-park-tracker demo-src. properties.js mock data needs 25 properties seeded across 10+ global cities.
- **Risks:** (1) World-zoom pin overlap mitigated by lat/lng jitter + zoom 3 start -- builder must verify visually during local QA. (2) Cormorant Garamond at very light weights may render poorly on Windows Chrome -- test at weight 300 vs 400, prefer 400 if thin renders weak. (3) 13 files is 1 over cap but justified; no further scope expansion.
- **Gate:** PLAN READY. No unknowns. Proceed to builder.
